nd more direct way to communicate with their constituents.             Essential reading for scholars of technology and European history, Europe-On Air reveals broadcast radio to be a technology that revolutionized international relations during the brief respite between the chaos of war in Europe.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aRadio broadcasting -- Europe -- History. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2002-2015z978311066278808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam Univ.Press  eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048516650423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048516650.jpg  a978-3-11-060651-5  Amsterdam Univ.Press  eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2002-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG